CommonFields.Title: Bimodal brush functionalized TiO2/silicone nanocomposites with improved dielectric properties
Author: Huang, Yanhui
Krentz, Timothy M.
Nelson, J. Keith
Schadler, Linda S.
Bell, Michael
Benicewicz, Brian
CommonFields.Location: Dept. of Materials Science and Engineering, Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute, Troy, NY USA

SolventAmount.description: 0.056 g of 9-anthracenemethylphosphonic acid was dissolved in 50 mL THF

Additive.Description: 1.0 g PDMS grafted TiO2 nanoparticles were added to the solution using an ice bath.

Mixing.Description: The mixture was warmed up to room temperature and stirred overnight.

ChooseParameter.Other: The nanoparticles were recovered by precipitation in methanol.

Mixing.Description: Spherical TiO2 NPs were synthesized using a two-phase thermal synthesis approach.35 In a typical synthesis, 0.4 mL of tert-butylamine was dissolved in 10 mL of DI water and the solution was transferred to a 45 mL stainless steel pressure vessel (Parr).
titanium(IV) butoxide (1 mL) and oleic acid (OA) (3 mL) were added into 20 mL toluene and homogeneously mixed.

Heating.Description: The organic mixture was then transferred to the pressure vessel without stirring. The pressure vessel was heated to 220 °C for 5 h and cooled to room temperature.

Additive.Description: The resulting TiO2 particles capped with oleic acid were precipitated with ethanol and recovered by centrifugation at 10 000 rpm for 10 min.

Drying-Evaporation.Description: Silicone rubber (Sylgard® 184 from Dow Corning) was used as the polymer matrix. Sylgard® 184 contains 40 wt% fumed silica as a reinforcing filler. The resin was dissolved in THF to mix with the TiO2 nanoparticles and then the solvent was removed under vacuum.

Amount.description: The cross-linker was added at a 10:1 weight ratio.

Mixing.Description: The cross-linker was added at a 10:1 weight ratio before shear mixing at 3500 rpm for 1 min.

Heating.Description: The resin was cast in a flat aluminum dish and cured at 110 C under vacuum for 1.5 h.

Transmission_Electron_Microscopy.Description: Transmission electron microscopy (TEM) sections were microtomed from samples at -140 0C with a thickness of 80 nm. The distribution of TiO2 nanoparticles in the silicone matrix was characterized from TEM images. The breakdown samples were 400 􀀃􀀁30 􀀂m thin films. The thickness at several points was measured with a micrometer before testing. The top electrode was made of stainless steel and is spherical with a diameter of 5 mm. The bottom electrode was the supporting aluminum dish on which the sample was cured. The tests were carried out in transformer-grade silicone oil to avoid flashover. The short term AC breakdown strength was measured by manually ramping the voltage at a rate of approximately 500 V/s, taking the maximum voltage as the breakdown voltage.

Dielectric_and_Impedance_Spectroscopy_An.Description: Dielectric spectroscopy measurements were carried out with a Novocontrol Alpha analyzer.

Pulsed_Electro_Acoustic.Description: The pulse electro-acoustic (PEA) test used an aluminum bottom electrode as ground and a carbon black loaded semi-conductive polymer top electrode. The applied voltage was DC, and the probe pulse had a width of 10 ns, a repetition frequency of 140 Hz, and an amplitude of 300 V.
